Package edu.trident.hilliard.finalassignment

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CabRecord
    Interface used by CabRecordManager to represent a single cab entry
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CabInfo
    Object responsible for managing records for each individual cab.

    Variables:
    cabName - name of cab
    CabRecordManager
    Uses CabRecord interface to create a specific type of CabRecord.
    Formats output with an overriden toString.

    Variables:
    recType - type of record
    cabDate - date of the record
    cabId - name of cab
    inputValue - number of gallons
    gasCost - cost of each gallon
    CabRecordReader
    Opens file at inputPath and reads records into an ArrayList.

    Variables:
    cabList - ArrayList of cabs
    FareRecord
    Object for handling CabRecords of the Fare type

    Variables:
    fareMiles - number of miles
    RIDE_RATE - constant value for initial ride charge
    RIDE_MILEAGE_RATE - constant value for per mile ride charge
    GasRecord
    Object for handling CabRecords of the Gas type

    Variables:
    gasGallons - number of gallons
    gasCost - cost of each gallon
    GenericCabRecord
    Generic record for cab data

    Variables:
    cabDate - record date
    RecordRunner
    Gathers input and output file names, sets defaults values in project directory if user does not input values.
    RentedTaxi
    RentedTaxi extends Taxi with operating costs such as servicing and gas.
    ServiceRecord
    Object for handling CabRecords of the Service type

    Variables:
    serviceCost - cost of the service
    Taxi
    Taxi models a taxi with a set rate and mileage rate, gas mileage, and gas capacity as well as currentGas, currentMileage, and totalFare to track information related to the specific taxi.

    Variables:
    RIDE_RATE - constant value for initial ride charge
    RIDE_MILEAGE_RATE - constant value for per mile ride charge
    GAS_MILEAGE - constant value for gas mileage of cab
    GAS_CAPACITY - constant value for capacity of the cab's gas tank
    currentGas - amount of gas in the cab
    currentMileage - distance the cab has traveled
    totalFare - accumulated total of fares
    TaxiUI
    TaxiUI creates and populates a JFrame with 3 JTextFields for GasInput, Input, and Output, a combo box and button to provide functionality of recording trips and adding gas, reporting gas, distance.

    Variables:
    currCab - RentedTaxi object that is currently selected in the UI
    cabList - ArrayList of CabInfo records
    cabs - ArrayList of RentedTaxi objects
    cabDate - initialized as the last date of the cab
    SERVICE_COST - constant value for the cost of servicing a cab
    cabListPosition - tracks which cab is currently selected in the combo box
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
